NovaPay — local setup (plain text; extend this file instead of adding new .md)

All-in-one Docker stack (app + Postgres + Redis + RabbitMQ):
  From nova-pay repo root:
    ./run-dev.sh
  Compose file: docker/docker-compose.yml  ·  image: docker/Dockerfile
  A one-shot `migrate` service runs `npm run migration:run` after Postgres is healthy,
  then the API container starts (DATABASE_SYNCHRONIZE=false — schema from migrations only).

Local DB without Docker:
  export DATABASE_WRITE_URL=postgresql://... && npm run migration:run

Workspace Postgres (primary + replica, optional — use when you need replica ports 5432/5433):
  From repo root: cd ../infra/postgres
  cp .env.example .env && docker compose up -d
  Point nova-pay/.env DATABASE_* at those URLs (see infra/postgres README).

App env (non-Docker or custom):
  Copy nova-pay/.env.example to .env; set DATABASE_WRITE_URL / DATABASE_READ_URL and
  RABBITMQ_URL / REDIS_URL to match your brokers.

Run API without Docker:
  cd nova-pay && npm ci && npm run start:dev

Swagger (default PORT from .env):
  http://localhost:3002/api (see PORT in .env.example)

Architecture rules for agents:
  .cursor/rules/nova-architecture.md
  .cursor/rules/global.md
